{{Other places|Ahern Glacier (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Ahern Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Ahern Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = tributary | location = [[Ross Dependency]] | coordinates = {{coord|81|47|S|159|10|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline, title}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Starshot Glacier]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Ahern Glacier''' is a small [[tributary]] [[glacier]] flowing east from the [[Churchill Mountains]] between [[Mount Lindley]] and [[Mount Hoskins]] to enter [[Starshot Glacier]]. It was named by the Holyoake, Cobham, and Queen Elizabeth Ranges Party of the [[New Zealand Geological Survey Antarctic Expedition]] (1964&ndash;65) for B. Ahern, a member of the party.
