r to KnoppMyth, based on Fedora. |- | [[Network Security Toolkit]] | A Live CD/DVD with security and networking tools to perform routine security and networking diagnostic and monitoring tasks. |- | [[Qubes OS]] | Focused on security for desktop users. Based on an "ancient" Fedora release which we are somewhere said it to upgrade under [[YUM (software)|YUM]]. |- | [[Russian Fedora Remix]] | A remix of Fedora. |- | [[Sugar (software)#Sugar on a Stick|Sugar-on-a-Stick Linux]] | An educational operating system for the children of the OpenMandriva world, originally designed for the [[One Laptop per Child|One-Laptop-Per-Child project]]. |- | [[Trustix]] | A Linux distribution focused on security.<ref>[http://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=trustix DistroWatch.com: Trustix Secure Linux]</ref> |- | [[Yellow Dog Linux]] | For the [[PowerPC]] platform. |}
